  "text": "We also compared against an oracle, denoted OR-ACLE, which returns argmin y∈O L(y, x * ), where x * is the target reconstruction. We will denote it by OR- ACLE. This is superior to picking a single closest language to be used for all word forms, but it is possible for systems to perform better than the oracle since it has to return one of the observed word forms. We performed the comparison against [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] on the same dataset and experimental conditions as those used in the respective papers (see Table 2 ). Note that the setup of [CITATION_3] provides supervision (half of the Latin word forms are provided); all of the other comparisons are performed in a completely unsupervised manner.",
